    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "@ratacat , don't worry too much, because TG's database (LMDB) is basically is MMAP file. MMAP file performance heavily rely on OS page cache (aka \"virtual memory of process\") and OS will use all available RAM for this and elastically free it if RAM is needed in another part of system at the moment. So, TG will use all your RAM, but this memory will belongs to OS instead of TG.\r\nin short - for now, stick with defaults is good enough.\r\n\r\ncores - here we are less effitient for now, only few parts of TG are using multi-core. Most of TG is single-core, but it's not because it lack parallelism, but because it is Disk bounded - not CPU bounded, and adding parallelism to Disk-bounded tasks will make things worse. But Raid may help here - see more info about it in our #testing chat.",
